Reasoning: The paper analyzes the decay process of online social networks and uses statistical analysis and machine learning to predict cascade size and virality. This work falls under the scope of social computing (cs.SOC) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the use of machine learning for prediction suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis of network measures and patterns also relates to cybernetics (cs.CYBER). Finally, the focus on community dynamics and member behavior aligns with the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
